Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows significant renal impairment (elevated creatinine), mild hypoglycemia, and mildly elevated ALT suggesting possible hepatic involvement. Other parameters, including electrolytes, proteins, and lipid profile, are within normal limits. Clinical correlation and further evaluation of renal and liver function are recommended.
